Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Put a large #saucepan{} of water to
the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces and pop onto a #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

When the aubergine is halfway through cooking, add the pepper chunks to the same
baking tray, drizzle with a little more oil and toss together. Cook for the remaining
time, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when the water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%grams} and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} to the pan and season
with salt and pepper. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes with
basil{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and the
@sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until
thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the sauce simmers, drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid
as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with
oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

When everything's ready, remove the roasted veg from the oven and turn your grill on
to high.

Stir the roasted veg and cooked penne into the tomato sauce. Stir in the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and the @butter{20%grams} until melted.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it
needs it.

Transfer the pasta mixture to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and top evenly
with the mozzarella.

Pop under your hot #grill{} until the cheese is bubbling and golden brown,
~{7-8%minutes}.

Once the ratatouille pasta al forno is ready, share between your serving bowls and
tuck in. Enjoy!